is technique, i do it at home. except i don't hit my head when i do it. she was honestly giving me a headache and i had to speak up and tell her she was hurting me. and trust me, i'm not one to speak up unless something is really bothering me. she asked me rudely if it hurts when she brushed my hair. um, no, not when you don't hit my head with the hair brush! in the end my haircut was decent, mediocre. she only took off one inch (i had asked for two) so i will have to get my hair cut again soon. i could have received the same haircut and probably better service by paying half as much at supercuts.", "business_id": "rmiYCZaCoqNysrxAnEhbgA", "stars": 2, "date": "2010-08-26", "type": "review"}